{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "13", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "08", "M": "31", "S": "00"}}, "news": [{"title": "MMRDA receives three bids to prepare Mumbai metro 14 DPR", "para": "MMRDA is revising the Detailed Project Report for Metro Line 14 connecting Kanjurmarg and Badlapur after failing to attract private developers for a PPP model. The authority is now exploring an EPC route with institutional loans and a deferred payment structure for the \u20b918,000 crore project.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/mumbai-metro-line-14-receives-bids-as-mmrda-revises-project-financing/131058607?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-130518/131058607.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "About 5,500 residential, commercial units in Ahmedabad identified as bulk waste generators", "para": "Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation is enforcing new waste management rules for large waste generators. Over 5,500 societies and complexes must process biodegradable waste on-site and segregate dry waste. This aims to reduce landfill pressure and protect the environment. Institutions have one year to comply. Failure to do so will result in strict action.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/ahmedabad-municipal-corporation-targets-5500-bulk-waste-generators-to-enhance-solid-waste-management/131058551?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-2276395/131058551.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Against 3,600 PMAY applicants, only 130 pay 10% margin money in Sambhajinagar", "para": "Slow progress plagues the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana in Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar, with a mere 130 out of 3,638 applicants submitting the mandatory margin money. To accelerate the scheme, the